                },
                "message": "Escape module string when importing class from unicode module\n\nI don't think this is is an important fix, because most compilers\ndo handle unicode characters in strings. However, we do generally\ntry to generate ASCII C code for maximumum compatibility.\n\nI also made sure they're definitely encode as UTF-8 since\nthat's what the Python C API functions expect. It's\npossible that this might have caused an issue if the\nCython source files were encoded with something else but I'm\nnot sure I can test that in srctree.",
